[34mAnxiety is one of the most common mental health problems in the UK and[0m
[34mit is increasing. Yet it remains under-reported, under-diagnosed and under-[0m
[34mtreated. A good ability to cope with anxiety is key to resilience in the face of[0m
[34mwhatever life throws at us. However, experiencing it too much or too often means we risk becoming overwhelmed, unable to find balance in our lives[0m
[34mor to relax and recover. Our ability to find some inner peace has never[0m
[34mbeen more important to our well-being.[0m
[34mThis report is about framing anxiety as an essential aspect of our humanity[0m
[34mand part of the natural human emotional response to circumstances in our lives. It is also about challenging the stigma that still gets in the way of our[0m
[34mreaching out for help and support when our levels of anxiety become a real[0m
